efs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsionQuot\">IsTorsionQuot</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">L</span> ⊓ <span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">F</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsionQuot\">IsTorsionQuot</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">L</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Intersecting the left ideal with `K` does not change `IsTorsionQuot` on the right.\nIn particular, `IsTorsionQuot F L K` need not require `L ≤ K` for it is equivalent to asserting\nthe quotient `K / (L ⊓ K)` is `F`-torsion. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.isTorsionQuot_inter_left_iff","kind":"theorem","line":100,"name":"IdealFilter.isTorsionQuot_inter_left_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.lean#L100-L110"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsionQuot\"><span class=\"name\">IdealFilter</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsTorsionQuot</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter\">IdealFilter</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">L </span><span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that the quotient `K/L` is `F`-torsion if every element `k ∈ K` is annihilated\n(modulo `L`) by some ideal in `F`. Equivalently, for each `k ∈ K` there exists `I ∈ F`\nsuch that `I ≤ L.colon {k}`. This formulation avoids forming the quotient module explicitly. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsionQuot","kind":"def","line":94,"name":"IdealFilter.IsTorsionQuot","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.lean#L94-L98"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsion\"><span class=\"name\">IdealFilter</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsTorsion</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter\">IdealFilter</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommMonoid\">AddCommMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Module-level `F`-torsion: every element is `F`-torsion. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsion","kind":"def","line":89,"name":"IdealFilter.IsTorsion","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.lean#L89-L92"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsionElem\"><span class=\"name\">IdealFilter</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsTorsionElem</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter\">IdealFilter</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommMonoid\">AddCommMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\">M</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that an element `m : M` is `F`-torsion if it is annihilated by some ideal belonging to\nthe filter `F`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsTorsionElem","kind":"def","line":83,"name":"IdealFilter.IsTorsionElem","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.lean#L83-L87"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/IdealFilter/Basic.html#IdealFilter.IsUniform.colon_mem\"><span class=\"name\">IdealFilter</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsUniform</span>.<span class=\"name\">colon_mem</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span 